/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999782557178477, \"rank\": 1.964756561450122e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1028, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999990733446994, \"rank\": 8.217603574964473e-07, \"text\": \"ancient Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the host the2024\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 872}, {\"ngram\": \"Summer Games\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 885}, {\"ngram\": \"ahat\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"liberty\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"freed slaves\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1081}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Salt Lake City hosted the2002 Winter Games, atrio of cartoonish crittersfound in Utah were selected as mascots: Powder, the snowshoe hare; Copper, the coyote; and Coal, the black bear, all named for Utah's natural resources.\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1089, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.5826862743143224, \"rank\": 0.7161893859847108, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999998640491959, \"rank\": 9.45634544269609e-08, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U